34:37.460 --> 34:39.286
Hello?

34:41.000 --> 34:42.199
Hello?

34:42.199 --> 34:43.458
- Hi.
- Hi.

34:43.460 --> 34:44.969
Ooh, it's a little poochy.

34:44.969 --> 34:47.699
Poochy! What a beautiful dog.

34:47.699 --> 34:49.319
Oh, you... whoo!

34:49.320 --> 34:50.899
He likes me.

34:50.900 --> 34:54.051
My name is Alma Lane and I
am so sorry to disturb you,

34:54.052 --> 34:56.819
but my cat, Carleton, he's gone missing,

34:56.820 --> 34:59.649
and I'm passing out some flyers.

34:59.650 --> 35:01.829
This is my little Carleton...

35:01.830 --> 35:03.399
- a bit of a wanderer.
- _

35:03.400 --> 35:06.459
Usually, I'm not concerned,
but it's been over a week now.

35:06.460 --> 35:08.679
Have you seen him?

35:08.680 --> 35:10.499
I'm sorry, no.

35:10.500 --> 35:12.259
It's just not like him

35:12.260 --> 35:14.340
to stay away this long.

35:17.620 --> 35:19.785
Are you all right, dear?

35:20.980 --> 35:23.719
I'm fine.

35:23.720 --> 35:25.240
Why are you staring at me?

35:25.248 --> 35:26.809
Oh, I don't mean to.

35:26.810 --> 35:28.369
I'm sorry.

35:30.780 --> 35:33.539
Truth be told, I'm a little psychic.

35:33.540 --> 35:37.039
I walked up here worried about my cat.

35:37.040 --> 35:39.221
Now I'm a little worried about you.

35:43.370 --> 35:45.267
You need to be pretty.

35:47.104 --> 35:49.429
And not too twitchy.

35:49.430 --> 35:53.199
I don't find you twitchy in a bad way,

35:53.200 --> 35:55.859
but I need you to be
comfortable in your own skin

35:55.860 --> 35:57.529
in a way that...

35:59.860 --> 36:01.576
